def: Of or pertaining to a smock; resembling a smock; hence, of orpertaining to a woman. Smock mill, a windmill of which only the capturns round to meet the wind, in distinction from a post mill, whosewhole building turns on a post.-- Smock race, a race run by women for the prize of a smock. [Prov.Eng.]
The Angora goat. See Angora goat, under Angora.
A projecting piece of timber or iron near the bow of vessel, towhich the anchor is hoisted and secured.
A small wooden vessel made of staves and hoops, like a tub.[Prov. Eng.]
The state of being pure (in any sense of the adjective).
The quality or state of being rich (in any sense of theadjective).
